[This report confirms something I have suspected for some time that Western
Canadian cases of livestock anthrax might get recycled when the processors
are unaware of the cause of death. One of the Canadian strains kills cattle
without any extravasation of blood ... the textbook "red flag" on anthrax
as a cause of sudden death in cattle. It can be but in some regions it is
rarely seen. - MHJ
